author: djames
msg: Always build SWIG headers in the build dir, unless we are still using
pristine SWIG headers from an official Subversion release.
* Makefile.in:
(SWIG_INCLUDES): Look in build dir and build-proxy dir for SWIG files.
(EXTRA_SWIG_PROXY_FILES): A list of the manually-managed autogenerated
SWIG proxy files.
(extraclean-swig-headers): Add target. Removes manually managed
autogenerated SWIG files from source dir.
(clean-swig-headers): Don't remove header files from source directory.
Instead, remove manually managed autogenerated SWIG files from the build
dir, if the build dir is different from the source dir.
(SWIG_PY_DIR/__init__.py): Remove target.
(copy-swig-py): Copy python files from the source dir to the build dir.
(swig-py): Add copy-swig-py as dependency. Remove SWIG_PY_DIR/__init__.py
as dependency, because copy-swig-py replaces this target.
(clean-swig-py): Don't delete *.c files. Delete *.py files from build dir if
the build dir is different from the source dir.
(clean-swig-rb): Don't delete *.c files.
* subversion/bindings/swig/perl/native/Makefile.PL.in: Don't delete *.c files.
* build/generator/gen_make.py:
(write): Don't clean autogenerated header files from source dir in clean-*
targets. Instead, clean them in extraclean-* targets. If the source dir is
different from the build dir, clean autogenerated header files from build
dir in clean-* targets.
(write_standalone): Set the build directory to be the same as the source
directory if we are generating headers for the purpose of release mode.
Suggested by: philip
